<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/230: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-20T18:00:00-05:00">December 20, 1937—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>62. Your telegram no. 89, December 8, 11 a.m. Please telegraph status of
                                <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> negotiations and why there has
                            apparently been a delay in the exchange of ratifications of the
                            Franco-Chilean commercial treaty.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>